The Hotel is a Palazzo, we stayed in a very nice suite with views of the pool and gardens, classic style mixed with plasma and bang & olufsen music equipment (nice blend).	5 star elegance here that some might find 'traditional' in style - but that I liked, as it had not succumbed to a 'contemporary' makeover.	Breakfast was good - usual continental style plus scrambled eggs and bacon, cereals, fresh fruit and champagne!